### Create a route mapping

```
Definition
```

```http
POST /v3/route_mappings HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/route_mappings" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "relationships": {
      "app": {
        "guid": "[app-guid]"
      },
      "route": {
        "guid": "[route_guid]"
      }
    }
  }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_route_mapping %>
```

#### Required Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
**app** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | A relationship to an app.
**route** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | A relationship to a route.

#### Optional Parameters

Name | Type | Description | Default
---- | ---- | ----------- | -------
**app_port** | _integer_ | The port that traffic will be routed to for the mapped process. | `8080`
**process** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | A relationship to a process. This relationship is specified by `type` instead of `guid`.
